name: Children’s Christmas Program: “The Birth of Jesus”
Christmas Day Service of Lessons and Carols
description: This year Christmas Day falls on a Sunday and so we will gather for worship as we normally do. This service will be a service of readings and carols and will continue our celebration of Jesus’ birth from the night before.

name: Movie Night
description:

A Christmas Movie for the whole family will be announced - watch for the information to come!. Any ideas for a movie??? Suggestions are welcome!

Invite friends, family and neighbors for a night out at the movies - plus some popcorn, fellowship and some fun viewing.

name: Walk for Warmth
description: The location for this year?s Walk for Warmth has been changed to Great Lakes. This event, sponsored by the Oakland Livingston Human Service Agency raises funds for emergency utility assistance for those in need. In the past we have had a team of “Holy Strollers” participating. You may sign-up Sundays at worship or call the church office. If you cannot walk in the event please support someone who is.

name: Ash Wednesday Service
description: Lent is a special time of the church year that calls us to focus on the quality of the life of our faith. It asks us to not just to „give something up? but add something to our life that will help us spiritually grow. Our Ash Wednesday service will include the imposition of ashes as a sign of our willingness to turn away from things that draw us from God, and toward those things that will draw us closer to God. Holy Communion will also be celebrated. See inside this newsletter for more opportunities to grow this Lenten Season.

name: Men of Grace
description: Leading us in worship on this Sunday will be the Men of Grace, a musical and witnessing ministry of Grace Gospel Fellowship in Pontiac. This musical ministry is made up of men who have completed one year of rehabilitation program at the Grace Centers of Hope and testify to the power of God to change lives. Their musical style is gospel-blues jazz with emphasis on vocal harmony. Musical selections will include spiritual, traditional and contemporary expressions. Invite family and friends and join us for this special time of worship and praise.

name: Worship Service - Graduate Recognition
description:
During the worship service we will recognize our high school and college graduates
congratulating them on their accomplishment, and asking God’s blessings on them as they plan future endeavors. A list of graduates that we have received is included in this newsletter. If you are not listed or know of someone, please contact the church office. Also, we request that graduates contact the church office to let us know if you will be present for worship this day.

name: Semi-Annual Meeting
description: All confirmed members of the congregation are requested to remain at the church for the congregational meeting following the worship service this day. We will be electing or reelecting three members to our congregational council. Those who have an interest in serving on council should contact pastor or council president, Gerry Cleasby. The election will be the main item on the agenda. A mission and financial update will also be presented.

description:

are invited to join the meetings on Wednesdays, June 6 and 13th at 7:00 pm.
New members will be received on Sunday June 17th with the Welcome Supper to be
held Tuesday June 19 at 6:30 pm. Please contact Pastor Negele or call the church office for more information.

description:
BURGER BAR - Youth Fund Raiser!
The youth are trying to get the BURGER BAR organized to help fund their events. The BURGER BAR is Friday, June 15th before the Free Movie Night! Come for a night out -Dinner & a Movie and help support our Youth!

name: FREE Movie
description:
FREE MOVIE NIGHT - Friday, June 15 at 7:00 pm

The Outreach and Communications Ministry aresponsoring free Movie Nights - all are welcome. Watch for the information to come!. Any ideas for a movie??? Suggestions are welcome! Invite friends, family and neighbors for a night out at the movies - plus some popcorn, fellowship and some fun viewing.

name: Rally Day
description: The fall season gets underway with many of our activities resuming this month. We invite everyone to rally at the church this second Sunday of September for worship and a church picnic to follow. This year the picnic will be held on church grounds with food, games and fun planned for everyone, including a bounce house for kids. See inside this newsletter for more details. Join us for this time of fun and fellowship and getting the fall season kicked off to a great start. Feel free to wear picnic type clothes to church on this day!

name: Faith & Politics with Light Supper Provided
Service of Lessons and Carols
description: The Chancel Choir will help inspire our Christmas preparations with this service filled with beautiful anthems, familiar carols, and Scripture readings. It is a service that tells the story of Christmas through both word and song. Invite your family and friends to join us for this meaningful service at our regular worship time, 10:00am

name: Sunday School Christmas Program
description:
“The Wisdom of the Pine”

The children of the church will be sharing the Christmas message at this service at 10:00am. In their own unique way the Christmas story will be told. Again, invite family and friends to come and share in this program. Watch for a rehearsal schedule to be announced.

name: Christmas Service
description: Join us to proclaim the joyous news of the birth of our Lord at one of our candlelight services. Each of these services will be filled with the joyous carols of Christmas, anthems by our choirs, holy communion, and the Christmas story according to St. Luke. At the 7:00pm service a Christmas message will be added for the children. Each service ends in the traditional candle lighting ceremony as the congregation sings “Silent Night.” Oh, come, let us adore him, Christ, the Lord!

name: Christmas Service

All Saints Sunday
description:
On this Sunday we remember the saints who have gone before us who have faithfully served
our Lord, and celebrate those living saints who continue to share in the work of God’s
church. Names of members who have died since the last All Saints Day will be added to our
All Saints Banner. In our prayers we invite you to share the names of loved ones that you
would like to remember. Join us this day as part of God’s great communion of saints.

name: Youth Worship Service
description:
Gather with us on this Sunday as our young people will lead us in worship. A message of
“thanksgiving” will be shared in Scripture readings, various skits, as well as music and song.
Let’s be supportive of our youth and join them in worship, praise and thanksgiving.

name: Adult Discussion
description:
We invite all to join us for these informal
discussions that will focus on various issues of
the day. Topics will be announced a week to
two weeks prior to the meeting time. We hope
to look at various sides of an issue and see how
our faith and biblical traditions can inform our
understanding. We welcome various voices and
perspectives no matter what the issue may be.

name: Thanksgiving Eve Service
description:
The familiar Thanksgiving hymn says it all, “Now thank we all our God, with heart and
hands and voices.” Let’s not leave God out of Thanksgiving. Before you gather around your
thanksgiving table with loved ones and friends, join us Thanksgiving Eve to thank the One
from whom all blessings flow. Let’s also be mindful of those in need and fill up our food
basket this day.

name: Chili Cook-Off
description: Chili Cook-off - February 15, 6:00 pm. Please sign up on your Information Slip and/or the poster in the Fellowship Area. $5.00 per person (no charge if you bring a pot of chili) or $15 per family. Contact Cindy Edwards or Deanna Mitchell with questions.

name: WELCA
description:
All WOMEN are invited to the WELCA Meetings - usually the first Thursday of each month at 10:00 am. There is a short meeting followed by a Bible Study lead by Pastor Negele. At noon each attendee brings a sandwich and a dessert and beverage is provided by that month’s hostess. Also the 2nd and 4th Tuesdays of the month at 9:00 am they gather to make quilts which are shipped to Lutheran World Relief to assist with diasters around the world.
Come and join in!

name: Men's Food & Fellowship
description: MEN’S FOOD & FELLOWSHIP is Monday, February 17th. ALL Men are invited to this monthly potluck held here at church. Those with last names beginning with A - I please bring a meat dish; J - Q a dessert and R -Z a salad. Be sure to sign up on your Information Slip of call the church office.

name: Early Easter Service
description: Our Lenten journey is complete. The Cross is not the final destination! Jesus is Alive! He is Risen! The journey ends with new life. Come celebrate with us at one of our joyous Easter Services. Please note the change of service times. The candles will be lighted, the flowers will be blooming, the bells will be ringing, the choir will be singing – all our senses will be celebrating this glorious day. Holy Communion will be celebrated at both services and a special Easter message for children will be shared at the 10:30am service.

name: Easter Breakfast
description: The EASTER BREAKFAST will again be part of our Easter Celebration. If you can help in any way - please indicate on your Information Slip, call the church office or Max Thompson. We will be needing donations of cut-up fresh fruit, coffee cakes & breads. You can sign up on your Information Slip what you will be able to bring.

name: Easter Egg Hunt
description: We hope to have the Annual EASTER EGG HUNT for the children. But.... we need someone to put it together. If you can help with this - please call Pat Scott or the church office. Going with the hope someone will come forth, we are asking for small toys (that would fit into plastic eggs) and small wrapped candy. Plastic eggs are not needed as we have several tubs of eggs stored.

description: Our Lenten journey is complete. The Cross is not the final destination! Jesus is Alive! He is Risen! The journey ends with new life. Please bring a snack to share. Be sure to sign up on your Information Slip or call the church office - and bring a friend!

name: Communion Baptism Service
description:
Mother's Day Tribute - The youth will offer a tribute for all moms during the worship service and a gift of flowers.

Special Noisy Offering - This month Noisy Can Offerings will resume.  The May Offering will help support the Eagle Scout Project of Jacen Schnitzer.

name: Graduate Sunday
description: We encourage any members who will be graduating from high school, college, or avocational school to join us for worship on this Sunday as they will be recognized for theiraccomplishments. Please contact the church office if you can be with us. Also, if you have afamily member that is graduating please let the church office know so that their name maybe included on the list of graduates. Congratulations to all and may God’s Spirit guide themin their decisions and future careers.

name: Confirmation Sunday
description: Students completing two years of confirmation instruction will be received into theconfirmed membership of the congregation on this Sunday during the worship service. Thisalso the festival of Pentecost celebrating the gift of the Spirit coming to the disciples ofJesus and forming the church. We celebrate the birth of the church as well as God’s Spiritworking in the lives of our young people who will be affirming their baptismal vows.

name: Yard Sale Take-In Begins
description:
Planning for the 2014 Yard Sale is in full swing and your help is always needed and appreciated, we have a job to fit your skills! Intake for church members will start on Sunday, June 8th and donations from the public, June 15th. Set up of tables will be the week before June 8th with Gerry Cleasby getting things down from the attic around June 2nd so please talk to him if you can assist with these jobs. We are also looking for someone to assist Don Scott with the “electronic” area outside before and during the sale. If you can help in this area, please let Gerry or Pat Scott know. Marking is planned for Monday and Wednesday mornings from 9-12 and
Tuesday and Thursday evenings from 6-8:30 pm, times may be adjusted as needed. Virla Cleasby will have a sign up sheet for cashiers on June 1st, so if you want to help out in this area, please see her. We are asking the congregation for donations of the following: masking tape, calculators (basic), poster board, new whistles, twine, empty boxes and sharpies for making. Please have these to church by June 8th so we know what we need to
purchase. A box will be there and marked with “donations for yard sale” on the box. We have instituted some parameters for pre sales this years, along with a sign up sheet for items that you may be on the look out for. More info on this will be forth coming. Our next meeting in June 18th at 6:00 pm, all are welcome and encouraged to attend. Thanks for your help and support with this endeavor. Gerry & Maggie

name: Men's Steak Fry
description: Men’s Annual Steak Fry is June 16th, 6:30 pm at Baycourt Park on Andersonville Rd. ALL MEN ARE INVITED. Those with last names beginning with A-M please bring a salad N -Z a dessert. Be sure to sign up so there will be enough for all. A fee will be collected that evening to cover the expenses.

Or simply call the church office to make arrangements for drop-offs.Mention to friends and neighbors that we will take leftover items from neighborhood yardsales as well.

We also need an intake of volunteers to help work the days of the Yard Sale. A sign upsheet is posted in the Fellowship Area. Watch for announcements for the different areas thatworkers will be needed. Sorters and markers are needed for the days and weeks prior to thesale, during church office hours, or Tuesday and Thursday evenings. CROP WALK
description: Waterford Area Crop Walk Sunday, Oct. 5th Registration: 1:30pm  Walk: 2:00pm This year’s Crop Walk for Hunger hopes toraise $20,000 within our community. Four local food agencies as well as efforts around the world will benefit from this walk. The names of those walking are posted on the wall in the fellowship area. Please support them. Sponsor forms are still available for those who would like to walk. Several routes may be walked: 5.5 mile, 3.5 mile, 1 mile, and a rocking chair. Let’s all help in combating hunger in our community and in the world. Contact Pastor or Norm Kingston for mmoreinformation.

name: Communion Worship Service - WELCA SUNDAY
description: On this special Sunday the women of the church serve as the worship servants.  ALSO - the quilts which have been constructed through the year for Lutheran World Relief will be displayed in the sanctuary for all to admire. Thank you ladies for all you do! Incidently - ALL women of Christ Lutheran are members of WELCA - notj ust those to attend the monthly meetings which we wish more would become involved.

name: 70th Anniversary Worship Service
description: All are welcome to join us to celebrate 70 years of ministry in Waterford Township. This Sunday is also Reformation Sunday for which the color of the day is red, symbolizing thefire of the Holy Spirit working within the church, and inspiring Martin Luther, back in 1517, to initiate reform within God’s church. We invite you to wear something red to symbolize that that same Spirit has worked through this congregation for 70 years and continues toinspire us to engage in God’s work. A variety of historical displays will be in the fellowshiparea, and various historical pictures will be viewed on the video screen. Be sure to indicate whether you will be able to join us for the luncheon following theservice in the lower level. Sign-up on the bulletin information slip on Sundays, or call thechurch office.  At the luncheon we will be sharing memories, giving thanks for God’sblessings, and enjoying  fellowship with one another. We also invite you to offer a special 70th Anniversary Gift to our Elevator Fund. SpecialAnniversary envelopes will be prepared for you to use. We invite you to give a multiple ofseven, ( $7, $70, or $700), or whatever you can. Join us in giving thanks for 70 years.

name: 70th Anniversary Luncheon
description: The 70th Anniversary Celebration Luncheonis Sunday, October 26 at Christ Lutheran after the worship service. Food & drinks will be provided.  Pleasesign up on your Information Slip andinclude how many will be attending AND if you will have a memory to share. Questions?  Please contact CindyEdwards (248-623-2907) or DeannaMitchell (248-683-5565)

name: Have a Happy and Safe NEW YEAR!
Have a Safe & Happy New Year!
Annual Congregational Meeting
description:
This is the official notice of the January Congregational Meeting that we are required to hold according to our constitution. This year’s meeting will be held in the lower level ofthe church where a luncheon will be served. Primary agenda items include the review of the Annual Reports, presentation and action on the proposed 2015 budget, consideration of a proposal on video upgrades, and sharing of thanksgivings.

All active confirmed members of the congregation are voting members and encouraged to be present for this important meeting that both celebrates our past ministry and looks forward to the future. All Team Ministries and organizations of the congregation are askedto submit a year- end report to be included in the Annual Report.

name: New Year Begins New Church Season
description: In the church year the Day of Epiphany marks the arrival of the Wisemen to the manger. The message of Epiphany is that the Christ-child is for all the world to behold. During theses Sundays of Epiphany we are reminded that God is a God for all people in all place sat all times.

name: Ash Wednesday
description:
Ash Wednesday marks the beginning of the season of Lent with the worship service at 7:00 pm. There will be a Lenten Supper at 6:00 pm prior to the Ash Wednesday Service. Please sign up if you plan to attend the supper. Pastor will be offering each Wednesday in Lent a devotional beginning at 7:00 pm. These will be preceded by a Soup & Sandwich Supper at 6:00 pm.

Help is needed:

The season begins with a service of ashes and confession reminding us of our mortality and dependence upon God. Our Lenten journey continues each Wednesday of the season beginning with a supper at 6:00pm

Early Easter Service
description: All are welcome to join with us in celebrating the Good News that Easter brings to all of our lives: “Because He lives we shall live also.” That is the promise given to us all. Because the grave and death could not hold our Lord, it will not hold us either. Come, join us in shouting the Easter proclamation: “Christ is Risen! He is Risen Indeed! Alleluia!”

name: Log Cabin Day
description: Several of our members participate in the Log Cabin Days sponsored by the Waterford Historical Society. You may want to check it out this weekend at the Fish Hatchery Park (4490 Hatchery Rd.). The event is free and there will be something for everyone in the family including historical displays of all kinds, arts and crafts, food, live entertainment, model steam trains, and live Alpacas.

name: First Communion Recognition
description: On this Sunday we will welcome to the Lord’s Table for the first time, five of our young people who have completed their First Communion instruction. They are: Chloe Anderson, Joey Combs, Drake Folsom, Kiiri Mason, and Abie Pennington. Our congratulations to them as we celebrate this important part of their journey of faith.

name: Mother's Day Tribute
description: Once again youth of the congregation will be offering a Mother’s Day tribute. Join us as we celebrate and give thanks for our moms, as well as all women who have taken on a mothering role in their lives. A special gift will be presented to each of the women present at our service.

name: New Member Sunday
description: On this Sunday we will welcome new members into the fellowship of our congregation. We celebrate their presence among us. New member orientation meetings are scheduled for Tuesday, May 5, and May 12, at 7:00pm. Those interested may still sign up for the meetings by contacting the church office.

name: Pentecost Sunday - Happy Birthday Church!
description: Pentecost marks the beginning of the Christian Church as the disciples of Jesus were empowered by God’s Spirit to spread the good news of the gospel to all the world. Lessons of the day will be read in different languages as the disciples of Jesus shared the good news in various tongues.

name: Holy Trinity Sunday
description: This Sunday recognizes the church’s teaching of the Holy Trinity, that God is experienced as Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, and yet is one God. It recognizes the mystery of the ways in which God has come to us, and how believers have witnessed to  God’s presence in their lives.

name: Men's Food & Fellowship
description: Will meet May 18 at 6:30 pm. All menare invited to this monthly potluck with good food and great fellowship. Those with last names beginning with A - I please bring a Meat Dish; J - Q a Dessert; and R - Z a Salad. Please sign up on your Information Slip on the preceding Sundays!

name: Spring Congregational Meeting
description: All voting members are asked to be present for this semi-annual congregational meeting. It will take place soon after our regular 10:00am worship service. There will be a brief break following the service and then voting members are requested to re-gather in the sanctuary for the meeting. We will need to elect four members to council for a two year term. If you are interested in serving on the council please contact Pastor or Gerry Cleasby, council president. We will also be sharing a financial update with regard both to our general operating fund and the elevator fund. All active confirmed members of the congregation are voting members.

name: Sunday School Recognition
description: Special thanks to our Sunday School Staff and Students for their participation in our Educational Ministry this past school year.

name: Graduate Recognition
description: We will honor graduates from high school, college/university, or vocational schools on this Sunday. Graduates will be asked to come forward and share future plans.

name: Father's Day Recognition
description: A Father’s Day tribute by our Youth.

description: You don’t need to know how to play, you can learn that night! Bring a snack to share. Please sign up on your Information Slip or the board in the fellowship area. Come & have fun! Family and friends are invited!

description: Save the Date! Trunk Junk SALE - Saturday, July 25. Save unneeded items to sell to help our local benevolence. Sell goods from your car trunk (or on a table) in our parking lot and donate some (or all) of the proceeds. Please see Mike Mitchell if you have any questions. If you need a table - please contact the church office.

name: Communion Worship (Noisy Offering to Support Carlee Cottrell)
description: This month’s noisy coin offering on Sunday, July 12, will be designated for the mission trip that Carlee Cottrell will participate in as part of the Indiana Wesleyan University Girls Basketball Team. The team is planning a trip to the Dominican Republic in August to participate in sporting ministries and service projects there. We invite your suport through this Noisy Offering, or you may designate on your offering envelope “Carlee Mission Trip.” Let's help her out on this most worthy cause.

name: Trunk Sale at Church
description: There is still time to sign up for this event and reserve a spot in the parking lot. If you need to clear out some stuff this is an opportune time to do it. Goods may be sold from the trunk of your car. You may reserve a table to display items. Mark prices on your own stuff. Donate a portion  or all of your earnings to our local benevolence fund which helps those in need within our community. A sign-up sheet is located on the counter in the fellowship hall. You are responsible to bring and remove your own stuff.

description:
Andy and Elisabete Nestor have invited church members to a picnic in their subdivision, Jayno Heights in Waterford. The picnic will be held at the Jayno Heights Beach Lot (3123 St. Jude Dr.). Hot dogs will be provided, please bring a dish to pass and a favorite beverage. And, of course a swimsuit. There is no life guard on duty. It should be a fun time for the whole family, especially if you have small children.

Please RSVP to Elisabete Nestor at 248-229-0993

The picnic will be on church grounds again this year with food and activities for all. It is a great time of fellowship to start off the fall season.

name: CROP Walk
description:
Join us for the annual hunger walk in our community. We hope to have over 100 walkers
Hit the streets of Waterford raising funds for hunger causes around the world. This year’s
goal is set at $15,000. As a congregation last year we led the way raising over $3600. There
will be
Three routes to choose to walk: a one mile, three mile and five mile. There will also be a
rocking chair available for those who may have difficulty walking.
Sponsor forms are available Sundays after worship, or contact the church office. If you
cannot walk please be sure to support someone who is. Local agencies that will benefit from
these funds are the Open Door Outreach Center of Waterford, Waterford Meals on Wheels,
Good Samaritan
Food Pantry of Pontiac, and the Baldwin Center of Pontiac.

name: WELCA Sunday
description:
(Women of the Evangelical Lutheran Church)

On this Sunday Women of the church will be recognized at the 10am Worship Service for the various ministries that they do for the church. Many of the quilts that have been completed over the past year will be on display in the sanctuary. These quilts will be given to Lutheran World Relief to serve those in need all around the world. A Temple Talk will be shared during worship outlining the various ministries of WELCA.
